[SN]TITLE[SN]
Fog 'could lead to travel delays' across parts of Wales

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Motorists could face potentially hazardous driving conditions and subsequent delays caused by fog, the Met Office has warned.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Parts of Wrexham, Powys and south east Wales are the areas most likely to be affected.
A yellow "be aware" warning is in place from 16:00 GMT on Sunday until 10:00 on Monday.
Forecasters said the "main uncertainty" surrounded whether the fog persists into the Monday morning rush hour.
